<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="85" type="derivation of specific epithet">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="85">Derivation of specific epithet.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="85">
The epithet 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“batesi”">
&quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">batesi</emphasis>
&quot;
</normalizedToken>
is an eponym, based on the family name of Henry Walter Bates, whose eleven years of collecting beetles in South America capturing adults of many new species, and genera such as this, would qualify him for the Hall of Fame of beetle collectors and describers, if there was such a Hall.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
